# Codex Argument — F1 fix (efficiency_ratio session isolation)

NOTE: This change was implemented directly by Claude at the user's explicit
request ("I fix it now"), overriding the normal audit-only role for this one
task. The audit that produced F1 is recorded in claudeArg (2026-05-23 full
broad audit).

Change made:

- `research_indicators.py`: `SignalEfficiencyRatio` was computed via
  `efficiency_ratio(rth["Close"], window=20)` on the multi-session RTH series
  WITHOUT session grouping. Because `efficiency_ratio` uses `series.diff(20)`,
  the first eligible signal bar (`SignalBarsSinceOpen == 19` == `SIGNAL_MIN_BARS`)
  reached one position back into the prior session, injecting the overnight gap.
  Fixed by adding `_session_efficiency_ratio` and computing it with
  `close.groupby(session).transform(...)`, matching the existing
  `_session_realized_volatility` / `_session_kyle_lambda` /
  `_session_return_autocorr` / `_session_rolling_variance_ratio` pattern.
- `tests/test_research_indicators.py`: added
  `test_efficiency_ratio_research_context_resets_at_session_boundary`, a
  two-session regression test. Verified it FAILS on the pre-fix code (boundary
  bar = 1.0, not NaN) and PASSES on the fix (boundary bar NaN). Single-session
  tests cannot catch this class of cross-session leak.

Why:

- Same Method-2 substrate family already fixed for RealizedVol / AutoCorr /
  VarRatio / Kyle. efficiency_ratio was the one price-change-derived column that
  was missed: no "does not reset" comment, no session-grouped caller.
- Measured impact on the prior clean artifact (discovery_20260522T145222Z):
  249/3585 trades (6.9%) at the boundary bar had a contaminated
  SignalEfficiencyRatio (mean 0.40 vs 0.30). Those are the SAME 249 trades where
  SignalRealizedVol is correctly NaN.

Effect of the fix:

- The 249 boundary trades now get NaN SignalEfficiencyRatio (correct — no full
  in-session 20-bar window yet), instead of a value biased high by the overnight
  gap. No other trade or any non-research column changes (efficiency_ratio is a
  research-only column joined by SignalTime; it does not drive entries/exits).

Tests:

- Full suite: 247 passed (was 246 + 1 new regression test).

